# ACCESSIBILITY RULES (FacePe)

## Semantic HTML

- **Header:** one per page; logo links to `/`.
- **Nav:** wrap primary links in `nav` with **visible label** (`aria-label="Primary"`).
- **Main:** exactly one `main` landmark wrapping all sections.
- **Footer:** `footer` with secondary nav.
- **Sections:** `section` + `aria-labelledby` referencing visible `h2`/`h3` ids.

## Keyboard

- **Skip link:** first focusable element on every page.
- **Drawer:** `Esc` closes; focus trap inside; return focus to menu button.
- **FAQ:** each question is a `button`; arrow keys optional enhancement only—**Tab** must work naturally.

## Focus

- **Visible ring:** `outline` or `ring-2 ring-brand-600 ring-offset-2` on all interactive elements (match purple brand, not browser default unless themed).
- **Never** `outline-none` without replacement.

## Color

- **Body text** `ink-body` on `surface-0` / `surface-page`: target **≥ 4.5:1** contrast.
- **`brand-600` on white:** verify **≥ 4.5:1** for small text; if not, reserve purple for **≥18px** bold or larger only.
- **Gradient buttons:** white text must meet **≥ 4.5:1** against **darkest gradient stop** (`#5000ea`).

## Images

- Meaningful images: descriptive `alt`.
- Decorative stars/lines/dividers: `alt=""` and `aria-hidden="true"`.
- **Hero:** `fetchpriority="high"` only for LCP image.

## FAQ / accordion

- `button` + `aria-expanded` + `aria-controls` pointing to `id` on answer panel.
- First item may be open by default: set `aria-expanded="true"` on that trigger.

## Motion

- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (see `docs/animation-system.md`).

## Forms (future CMS)

- Every input has visible `<label>`; errors tied with `aria-describedby`.

## DO NOT

- Remove focus outlines.
- Use color alone for state (underline links on hover/focus too).
- Create hover-only tooltips for critical info.
